## II. PHASE 15 DELIVERABLES

### A. [ideology_matrix.rs](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/ideology_matrix.rs) — The New Core Module

A pure, stateless module (zero side effects). Implements the full V15 Dispatch design:

| Function | Purpose |
|:---------|:--------|
| [resolve_flavor_label(x, y)](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/ideology_matrix.rs#98-123) | [(0,0)](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/main.rs#89-124) → *"Liberalism"*, [(-5,+5)](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/main.rs#89-124) → *"Stalinism"*, [(+5,-5)](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/main.rs#89-124) → *"Anarcho-Capitalism"* |
| [euclidean_distance(a, b)](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/ideology_matrix.rs#124-137) | 2D distance between ideological coordinates |
| [action_authority_cost(base, pos, target, fc)](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/ideology_matrix.rs#138-169) | `Base × (1 + dist × FC)` — the friction formula from V15 §IV |
| [check_zone_gates(pos)](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/ideology_matrix.rs#170-209) | Returns active `ZoneGate` variants for the current grid position |

**Zone Gates implemented:**

| Zone | Condition | Unlock | Disaster |
|:-----|:----------|:-------|:---------|
| Totalitarian Planned | `x < -3, y > +3` | Five-Year Plan | Bureaucratic Famine |
| Decentralized Laissez-Faire | `x > +3, y < -1` | Corporate Sovereign Zones | Plutocratic Secession |
| Illiberal Directed | `x ∈ [-3,0], y ∈ [+1,+3]` | State Champion Subsidies | Capital Flight |

### B. [state.rs](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/state.rs) — [IdeologyComponent](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/state.rs#26-51) Extended

Two new fields added with full doc-comments:

- **`position: (f64, f64)`** — Where the sovereign *actually governs* (policy track record).
- **`flavor_label: String`** — Live political archetype title for the HUD (e.g., *"Liberal Democracy"*).

These are **distinct** from [center](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/ideology_matrix.rs#344-349) (the faction-weighted Overton Window). The Euclidean gap between `position` and [center](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/ideology_matrix.rs#344-349) is **Ideological Tension** — a risk multiplier defined in `METRIC_DEFINITIONS.md §8`.

### C. [journey_tests.rs](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/tests/journey_tests.rs) — 4-Test Integration Suite

| Test | What It Validates |
|:-----|:------------------|
| [test_journey_populist_surge](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/tests/journey_tests.rs#48-121) | Single-actor Overton shift + estate-driven approval (Phase 14 regression) |
| [test_journey_three_actor_multipolar](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/tests/journey_tests.rs#126-299) | 3 actors (USA/CHN/ARG archetypes) — independent OW windows, divergent approval, zone gates, friction cost differential |
| [test_journey_ideology_matrix_labels](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/tests/journey_tests.rs#304-320) | 10 canonical grid coordinates verified against the Flavor CSV |
| [test_journey_zone_gate_activation](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/tests/journey_tests.rs#325-346) | All 3 zones, boundary exclusions, CHN position confirmed |

**On integration test scope (candid):** The 3-actor test validates simulation *math* across simultaneous actors — correct Overton derivation, approval weighting, zone gate activation, and friction cost differentials. It does not yet simulate *cross-actor behavioral dynamics* (diplomatic actions, faction contagion, proxy influence). That is `DIP-002` territory and requires the AI Director. The test is a permanent regression anchor for the political physics layer.

